    "updated_at": "2015-06-16T02:36:23Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Definitely looks like the scroll manager is being invoked, but like @Carreau says, it just listens to `space` and `shift-space`.  Could you have your machine mapping page up&down to those keys?\n\nAnyways, does the following code cell fix the problem for you?\n\n``` js\n%%javascript\nrequire(['notebook/js/scrollmanager'], function(sm) {\n    var NoScrollManager = function(notebook, options) {\n        sm.ScrollManager.apply(this, [notebook, options]);\n    };\n    NoScrollManager.prototype = Object.create(sm.ScrollManager.prototype);\n\n    NoScrollManager.prototype.scroll_some = function(pages) {\n        this.element.scrollTop(this.element.scrollTop() + pages * this.element.height());\n    };\n\n    IPython.notebook.scroll_manager = new NoScrollManager(IPython.notebook);\n});\n```\n"
  },
